Australia is home some of the biggest storms in the world, which unleash explosive energy that is equ
In the northern Australian territories, humid air hits heated land and is thrust upwards, rapidly cooling and condensing to form clouds that are taller than the world's highest mountains.Inside these clouds, electricity builds up on a monumental scale. The energy released from a single storm cell can be the equivalent to that of an exploding atom bomb.This astonishing storm was filmed for BBC Two'sWonders of the Monsoon.